      "verifier_files": [
        "cases/snapshot-signal-dispatch/verifier/signal.hidden.mjs"
      ],
      "task": "Users report that a listener which unsubscribes itself during emit can cause the next listener to be skipped. Before editing, run the included node repro/snapshot-signal.mjs and use its structured output to identify the first incorrect transition. Fix createSignal() so emit(value) dispatches synchronously in subscription order over an independent listener snapshot captured at the start of that emit. Unsubscribing during an emit affects only later emits, listeners added during an emit begin with the next emit, duplicate subscriptions remain independent, and every returned unsubscribe function is scoped and idempotent. Listener exceptions must stop dispatch synchronously and propagate unchanged. A nested emit must capture its own current snapshot without changing the outer snapshot. Preserve TypeError validation for non-function listeners, preserve the exact signal method and direct/public named export surfaces, and keep createSignal as a direct named export. Add focused regressions for self- and cross-unsubscribe, delayed additions, duplicate subscriptions, synchronous exception flow, nested emits, and subscription order. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
